<br>
However, no matter how bad it gets I will ONLY play an assassin, and right now what options do I have?  Go back to UO, go back to EQ, wait for the next on-line roll playing game?<br>
<br>
Good or bad, in my opinion DAOC is the best available at the moment.  So here I am.<br>
<br>
Also, sometimes great things happen that make it all worth it.<br>
<br>
The other night I was wandering the frontier, I am level 47.  I saw a yellow con Paladin.  I start running behind him unstealthed.  He knows I am there, but every time I close I hide.  He runs, I run. He stops, I stealth.<br>
<br>
Finally he decides that he can kill me.  He turns to face me, but I hide and keep moving towards him and to the side as much as possible.  I get behind him.<br>
<br>
He bows to where he last saw me, right as he comes up from his bow I hit him with Backstab and the Enervating poison.  After the stun wears off he turns to face me and to fight.  He gets a block in and I get an evade in, and we duke it out, sword to sword.<br>
<br>
In the end he dies.  I sit down next to his corpse with a little less than half my hit points left and I rest.<br>
<br>
That was a great moment.<br>
<br>
Another great moment happened a few weeks ago when I saw a yellow con enemy rogue near one of our frontier keeps.  I get behind him.  I stalk him up the hill towards the door.  There are about 10 or 15 of my realm mates standing there.  I hit Backstab and get a bonus crit of 350 damage, so I do a total of about 700 damage to this yellow con rogue.  He dies in one hit, I remain hidden, and everyone turns to look at his corpse.  I unstealth, bow to the crowd, stealth, and move on.  That was priceless.<br>
<br>
These little moments of sucess make all the struggles of leveling worth it.  <br>
<br>
Do I think the melee rogue needs help?  Hell yes!!  Do I think Mythic sucks for lying to us about disguise and our skills?  Hell yes!!<br>
<br>
But I keep on keeping on.  And I have to say I highly agree with one of the earlier posters that basically said it is best to avoid stress.  That is a HUGE issue for me.  I am trying to be happy and not let the bad things get me down too much.  Mythic doesn't care if I get angry, they don't respond when I complain, and as far as I can tell they don't give a rat's ass about the melee rogue community, but getting angry about all of that doesn't hurt them... it hurts me.<br>
<br>
Have fun.<br>
